<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFEarman.2C_J._and_Norton.2C_J.1999">Earman, J. and Norton, J. (1999). "Exorcist XIV: The Wrath of Maxwell's Demon. Part II. From Szilard to Landauer and Beyond". <i>Studies In History and Philosophy of Science Part B: Studies In History and Philosophy of Modern Physics</i> <b>30</b>: 1–40. <a href="/wiki/Digital_object_identifier" title="Digital object identifier">doi</a>:<span class="neverexpand"><a href="http://dx.doi.org/10.1016%2FS1355-2198%2898%2900026-4" class="external text" title="http://dx.doi.org/10.1016%2FS1355-2198%2898%2900026-4" rel="nofollow">10.1016/S1355-2198(98)00026-4</a></span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=Exorcist+XIV%3A+The+Wrath+of+Maxwell%27s+Demon.+Part+II.+From+Szilard+to+Landauer+and+Beyond&amp;rft.jtitle=Studies+In+History+and+Philosophy+of+Science+Part+B%3A+Studies+In+History+and+Philosophy+of+Modern+Physics&amp;rft.aulast=Earman%2C+J.+and+Norton%2C+J.&amp;rft.au=Earman%2C+J.+and+Norton%2C+J.&amp;rft.date=1999&amp;rft.volume=30&amp;rft.pages=1%E2%80%9340&amp;rft_id=info:doi/10.1016%2FS1355-2198%2898%2900026-4&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Maxwell%27s_demon"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span> also <a href="http://www.pitt.edu/~jdnorton/papers/ExorcistXIV/Exorcist2.pdf" class="external free" title="http://www.pitt.edu/~jdnorton/papers/ExorcistXIV/Exorcist2.pdf" rel="nofollow">http://www.pitt.edu/~jdnorton/papers/ExorcistXIV/Exorcist2.pdf</a></li>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFFeynmann.2C_R.P._.27.27et_al..27.271996">Feynmann, R.P. <i>et al.</i> (1996). <i>Feynman Lectures on Computation</i>. Addison-Wesley. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0140284516" class="internal">ISBN 0-14-028451-6</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Feynman+Lectures+on+Computation&amp;rft.aulast=Feynmann%2C+R.P.+%27%27et+al.%27%27&amp;rft.au=Feynmann%2C+R.P.+%27%27et+al.%27%27&amp;rft.date=1996&amp;rft.pub=Addison-Wesley&amp;rft.isbn=0-14-028451-6&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Maxwell%27s_demon"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span>, <i>pp</i>148-150</li>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFJordy.2C_W.H.1952">Jordy, W.H. (1952). <i>Henry Adams: Scientific Historian</i>. New Haven. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0685266834" class="internal">ISBN 0-685-26683-4</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Henry+Adams%3A+Scientific+Historian&amp;rft.aulast=Jordy%2C+W.H.&amp;rft.au=Jordy%2C+W.H.&amp;rft.date=1952&amp;rft.pub=New+Haven&amp;rft.isbn=0-685-26683-4&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Maxwell%27s_demon"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFLeff.2C_H.S._.26_Rex.2C_A.F._.28eds.292003">Leff, H.S. &amp; Rex, A.F. (eds) (2003). <i>Maxwell's Demon 2: Entropy, Classical and Quantum Information, Computing</i>. Institute of Physics. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0750307595" class="internal">ISBN 0-7503-0759-5</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Maxwell%27s+Demon+2%3A+Entropy%2C+Classical+and+Quantum+Information%2C+Computing&amp;rft.aulast=Leff%2C+H.S.+%26+Rex%2C+A.F.+%28eds%29&amp;rft.au=Leff%2C+H.S.+%26+Rex%2C+A.F.+%28eds%29&amp;rft.date=2003&amp;rft.pub=Institute+of+Physics&amp;rft.isbn=0-7503-0759-5&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Maxwell%27s_demon"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span>, <a href="http://www-users.cs.york.ac.uk/~susan/bib/nf/l/hrvyslff.htm#10345" class="external text" title="http://www-users.cs.york.ac.uk/~susan/bib/nf/l/hrvyslff.htm#10345" rel="nofollow">Contents</a> - an anthology and comprehensive bibliography of academic papers pertaining to Maxwell's demon and related topics. <a href="http://vlatko.madetomeasure.biz/Papers/maxwell2.pdf" class="external text" title="http://vlatko.madetomeasure.biz/Papers/maxwell2.pdf" rel="nofollow">Chapter 1</a> provides a historical overview of the demon's origin and solutions to the paradox.</li>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFMaxwell.2C_J.C.1871">Maxwell, J.C. (1871). <i>Theory of Heat</i>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Theory+of+Heat&amp;rft.aulast=Maxwell%2C+J.C.&amp;rft.au=Maxwell%2C+J.C.&amp;rft.date=1871&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Maxwell%27s_demon"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span>, reprinted (2001) New York: Dover, <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0486417352" class="internal">ISBN 0-486-41735-2</a></li>
